A struct groups named values into one new type.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    Player = |
        name String,
        score Int,
    |
]

Each field has a name and a type.

Fields can have defaults:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    Player = |
        name String,
        score Int = 0,
    |
]

`Player` is its own type. Another struct with the same fields is still a
different type.
